verage percentage.\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:49:- Dynamic-access coverage, including covered calls, total calls, coverage\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:51:  (§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage).\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:55:- Status, timestamp, library coordinate, strategy name, agent, model,\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:71:library with the configured strategy, and restore the repository state after the\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:80:- It ran several libraries and was part of a campaign covering many strategy\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:83:- Dynamic-access and code coverage metrics came from generated library stats,\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:85:- Cost, token, iteration, LOC, coverage, dynamic-access, metadata, status,\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:90:A benchmark result must not be used for strategy comparison when:\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:92:- It measured only one trivial library or one strategy in isolation.\n./forge/docs/benchmarking.md:94:- It lost token, cost, iteration, LOC, coverage, dynamic-access, or metadata\n./stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-xpath/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json:7:    \"strategy_name\": \"dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\",\n./stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-xpath/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json:16:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-xpath/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json:21:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-xpath/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json:55:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 21.61\n./docs/functional-spec.md:4:§GOAL-tested-metadata §GOAL-broad-version-coverage §GOAL-fresh-metadata §GOAL-protect-shipped-metadata\n./docs/functional-spec.md:23:| **Repository automation (Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/drivers/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/core/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/core/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/functional-spec.md](../forge/docs/functional-spec.md). |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:47:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` mirror of per-version metrics — `stats.json` (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information) produced by the harness, alongside the schema-validated `execution-metrics.json` each Forge run records.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:59:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:68:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:78:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/functional-spec.md:79:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/functional-spec.md:80:- `COVERAGE.md` — the per-library coverage table linked from the README. Each\n./docs/functional-spec.md:82:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/functional-spec.md:88:sync with the generated coverage table through the bulk-update PRs created by\n./docs/functional-spec.md:90:badge, graph, and history artifacts are published to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:96:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:99:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:110:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:114:| `fails-javac-compile` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed during the `compileTestJava` / Java compilation stage. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:118:| `fixes-javac-fail` | PR | PR repairs a `fails-javac-compile` compatibility issue. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:126:| `chunked-dynamic-access` | Issue | Forge split dynamic-access generation for this issue into class-aligned chunks because the uncovered class count exceeded the configured threshold. Normal project status controls whether Forge may claim the next chunk. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:127:| `human-intervention` | Issue / PR | Automation could not safely complete the work without manual follow-up, or automated PR review requested changes. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:128:| `human-intervention-fixed` | PR | Manual follow-up has fixed a PR previously requiring intervention; review automation may approve and merge it after merge gates pass. |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:220:- **Index coverage.** Each `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/` directory must include a valid `index.json` enumerating its metadata versions and tested library versions.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:232:- **Coverage non-regression.** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/functional-spec.md:262:- **Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:272:- For Forge: a predefined strategy name selecting workflow engine, agent,\n./docs/functional-spec.md:278:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:320:workflow logic, prompts, strategy, or deterministic harness support so the next\n./docs/functional-spec.md:354:§GOAL-broad-version-coverage §GOAL-fresh-metadata\n./docs/functional-spec.md:356:The repository must keep its tested-version coverage current as upstream\n./docs/functional-spec.md:424:the stage-specific `fails-*` label — `fails-javac-compile`, `fails-java-run`,\n./forge/docs/agent.md:4:interface, preserving the boundary in §AR-forge-strategy-agent-boundary.\n./forge/docs/agent.md:8:strategy (§STRAT-forge-predefined-strategy-contract).\n./forge/docs/agent.md:14:`@Agent.register(\"<name>\")`, and strategy loading resolves the configured\n./forge/docs/agent.md:15:backend by the strategy's `agent` field (see\n./forge/docs/agent.md:16:§STRAT-forge-predefined-strategy-contract).\n./forge/docs/agent.md:33:be selected through strategy data (§WF-forge-workflow-strategy-config) instead\n./forge/docs/agent.md:72:keeping the strategy/agent boundary intact (§AR-forge-strategy-agent-boundary).\n./forge/docs/agent.md:76:Forge prefers Pi for strategy profiles where it is sufficient because the\n./forge/docs/agent.md:78:coverage-positive automation that uses the least tokens needed for the task.\n./forge/docs/agent.md:86:- strategy data can select Pi without changing workflow code;\n./docs/tck.md:106:| `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`, `generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix` | Discover newer upstream versions and build the compatibility matrix (§GOAL-broad-version-coverage). |\n./docs/tck.md:108:## 8. Reporting, stats, coverage, and packaging\n./docs/tck.md:112:| `jacocoTestReport` | JaCoCo coverage for a coordinate. |\n./docs/tck.md:113:| `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess` | Dynamic-access coverage reporting (§FS-repository-functional-spec.4.5). |\n./docs/tck.md:114:| `generateLibraryStats`, `generateReadmeBadgeSummary`, `generateDependencyGraph` | Produce the stats mirror, README badge inputs, and dependency graphs that feed the coverage dashboard (§CI-publish-scheduled-coverage). |\n./docs/README.md:50:- [goals.md](goals.md) — the outcome goals: tested metadata, broad version coverage, fresh releases, and no regressions.\n./stats/org.apache.yetus/audience-annotations/0.12.0/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./forge/docs/workflows/workflow-drivers.md:13:   the predefined strategy bundle, instantiate the workflow engine, and create\n./forge/docs/workflows/workflow-drivers.md:25:predefined strategy configuration (§STRAT-forge-predefined-strategy-contract).\n./forge/docs/workflows/workflow-drivers.md:27:library-resolution task (§AR-forge-strategy-agent-boundary); it must not decide\n./forge/docs/workflows/workflow-drivers.md:46:- Load and validate the requested predefined strategy, including workflow,\n./forge/docs/workflows/workflow-drivers.md:54:- Build the workflow strategy object with the resolved paths, coordinate,\n./forge/docs/workflo